sentences: Brigitte François-Sappey (born 21 January 1944) is a French musicologist, educator, radio producer, and lecturer.
A professor of music history at the Conservatoire de Paris from 1973, she created the class of music culture in 1992, of which she is now an honorary professor.

She also founded the classes of art and civilization and history of music at the Conservatoire de Lyon (1979-1982) and musical analysis at the Conservatoire Rameau of the 6th arrondissement of Paris (1976–1979).
